
# Retail Sales Analytics with SQL

## Project Overview

This project is a SQL-based sales analytics case study using a simple **star schema** with one fact table (`sales`) and four dimension tables (`customers`, `products`, `stores`, `calendar`).  
The goal is to mimic a real-world retail business and use SQL to clean data and answer key business questions like **top products**, **customer spending**, and the **impact of discounts on quantity sold**.

## Dataset and Schema

The data is **dummy/synthetic**, created to resemble a multi-store retail business.  
It follows a standard **sales star schema** similar to many data warehousing assignments and portfolio projects.
